race.comment: Tough. LORD OF THE SUN (3) had been off the scene for 462 days but resumed further improved beaten a nose at Armidale. He tackled a CL3 here following, but mucked the start and was caught wide later. Suited stepping up to 1200m and he's proven third-up. Fitter again and the  2kg claim brings him right into it. AFRICAN DIAMOND (6) has been nudged out in her last two, with the latest at Gunnedah in a CL2 as a $2.0 favourite. Gibbons stays aboard and will give her every chance to go one better. MASTER GEE (1) has won his last two at this level and was heavily bet at Armidale last time. The 2kg claim takes care of most of the weight increase and from an inside gate he will get every chance to run out the extra 100m. BRIGHELLA (11) won a 50 here easily as expected and can feature with average luck in the run.
